time.py cmd/cli/tests/test_status_runtime.py -v` |\n554: | Phase 7 | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/ -k \"k8s_provider or agentcube_provider or publish_runtime or invoke_runtime or status_runtime\" -v` |\n555: | All Tests | `pytest cmd/cli/tests/ -v` |\n556: \n557: ---\n558: \n559: ## Acceptance Criteria\n560: \n561: - [x] `KubernetesProvider` class implemented with all API methods\n562: - [x] `KubernetesProvider.NODE_PORT_MIN` = 30000, `NODE_PORT_MAX` = 32767\n563: - [x] `KubernetesProvider.DEFAULT_TIMEOUT` = 120 seconds\n564: - [x] `KubernetesProvider._sanitize_name` follows Kubernetes naming conventions\n565: - [x] `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent` creates Deployment + NodePort Service\n566: - [x] `KubernetesProvider.wait_for_deployment_ready` polls until ready or timeout\n567: - [x] `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status` returns deployment and service status\n568: - [x] `KubernetesProvider.delete_agent` deletes Deployment and Service\n569: - [x] `AgentCubeProvider` class implemented with CR methods\n570: - [x] `AgentCubeProvider.CR_GROUP` = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"\n571: - [x] `AgentCubeProvider.CR_VERSION` = \"v1alpha1\", `CR_PLURAL` = \"agentruntimes\"\n572: - [x] `AgentCubeProvider.deploy_agent_runtime` creates AgentRuntime CR\n573: - [x] `AgentCubeProvider.get_agent_runtime` returns CR or None on 404\n574: - [x] `AgentCubeProvider.delete_agent_runtime` deletes CR with not_found handling\n575: - [x] `PublishRuntime` integrates both providers with provider selection\n576: - [x] `InvokeRuntime` integrates both providers with endpoint rewrite for AgentRuntime\n577: - [x] `StatusRuntime` integrates both providers with status retrieval\n578: - [x] All 23 KubernetesProvider unit tests pass\n579: - [x] All 20 AgentCubeProvider unit tests pass\n580: - [x] All 21 Runtime integration tests pass\n581: - [x] `KubernetesProvider` and `AgentCubeProvider` exported from services package\n582: \n583: ---\n584: \n585: ## File Changes Summary\n586: \n587: | File | Action | Lines | Description |\n588: |------|--------|-------|-------------|\n589: | `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | Created | 342 | KubernetesProvider implementation |\n590: | `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | Created | 190 | AgentCubeProvider implementation |\n591: | `cmd/cli/tests/test_k8s_provider.py` | Created | 373 | KubernetesProvider unit tests |\n592: | `cmd/cli/tests/test_agentcube_provider.py` | Created | 446 | AgentCubeProvider unit tests |\n593: | `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | Modified | 271 | Added provider integration |\n594: | `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` | Modified | 117 | Added provider integration |\n595: | `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` | Modified | 157 | Added provider integration |\n596: | `cmd/cli/tests/test_publish_runtime.py` | Created | 431 | PublishRuntime tests |\n597: | `cmd/cli/tests/test_invoke_runtime.py` | Created | 402 | InvokeRuntime tests |\n598: | `cmd/cli/tests/test_status_runtime.py` | Created | 506 | StatusRuntime tests |\n599: | `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/__init__.py` | Modified | 8 | Export providers |\n600: \n601: ---\n602: \n603: ## Implementation Notes\n604: \n605: ### KubernetesProvider Key Features\n606: \n607: - **NodePort Service**: Creates NodePort type Service for external access\n608: - **Deployment Management**: Creates/patches Deployments with env vars and entrypoint\n609: - **Readiness Waiting**: Polls deployment status with configurable timeout\n610: - **Error Handling**: Handles 409 (conflict) by patching, ignores 404 on delete\n611: \n612: ### AgentCubeProvider Key Features\n613: \n614: - **Custom Resource**: Uses CustomObjectsApi for AgentRuntime CR\n615: - **CRD Constants**: Defines group, version, plural for AgentRuntime CRD\n616: - **Readiness Probe**: Configures HTTP readiness probe with defaults\n617: - **ImagePullSecrets**: Sets default-secret for image registry auth\n618: \n619: ### Provider Selection Pattern\n620: \n621: ```python\n622: if provider == \"k8s\":\n623:     from agentcube.services.k8s_provider import KubernetesProvider\n624:     self._k8s_provider = KubernetesProvider(verbose=verbose)\n625: elif provider == \"agentcube\":\n626:     from agentcube.services.agentcube_provider import AgentCubeProvider\n627:     self._agentcube_provider = AgentCubeProvider(verbose=verbose)\n628: else:\n629:     raise ValueError(f\"Invalid provider: {provider}. Must be 'agentcube' or 'k8s'\")\n630: ```\n631: \n632: ### AgentRuntime Endpoint Rewrite\n633: \n634: For AgentRuntime CR invocations, the endpoint URL is rewritten:\n635: ```\n636: Original: http://api-server.example.com\n637: Rewritten: http://api-server.example.com/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{name}/invocations/\n638: ```\n639: \n640: ---\n641: \n642: ## Implementation Timeline\n643: \n644: | Phase | Tasks | Status | Completion |\n645: |-------|-------|--------|------------|\n646: | Phase 1: KubernetesProvider | T1.1-T1.11 | Done | 100% |\n647: | Phase 2: AgentCubeProvider | T2.1-T2.7 | Done | 100% |\n648: | Phase 3: K8s Tests | T3.1-T3.23 | Done | 100% |\n649: | Phase 4: AgentCube Tests | T4.1-T4.20 | Done | 100% |\n650: | Phase 5: Runtime Integration | T5.1-T5.8 | Done | 100% |\n651: | Phase 6: Runtime Tests | T6.1-T6.21 | Done | 100% |\n652: | Phase 7: Package Export | T7.1-T7.4 | Done | 100% |\n653: \n654: **Total Progress: 100% Complete (73/73 tasks)**\n655: \n656: ---\n657: \n658: ## References\n659: \n660: - Design: `changes/AR-026/design.md`\n661: - cli-toolkit/design.md — CLI toolkit architecture\n662: - cli-toolkit/spec.md — CLI specification\n\n(End of file - total 662 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider |\n| Module | `cmd/cli` |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n| Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: KubernetesProvider Implementation (ST-1)\n\n- [x] **T1.1**: Implement `KubernetesProvider.__init__` with namespace, verbose, kubeconfig params\n  - Purpose: Initialize provider with Kubernetes API clients (AppsV1Api, CoreV1Api)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-026/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775878901672,"end":1775878901688}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775878901718,"sessionID":"ses_2855e993bffex8QV8kEBx24qSH","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa18fbb001r0t366Nm47wiA6","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7aa1824e001nqJmBcmEYaDIt1","sessionID":"ses_2855e993bffex8QV8kEBx24qSH","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":16182,"input":893,"output":81,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":15208}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775878913023,"sessionID":"ses_2855e993bffex8QV8kEBx24qSH","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa1bbfb001TBKBUzQYFkfQEK","messageID":"msg_d7aa18fed001T0FSdcfzPD9VsD","sessionID":"ses_2855e993bffex8QV8kEBx24qSH","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775878917527,"sessionID":"ses_2855e993bffex8QV8kEBx24qSH","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa1c9a7001khyrzTsME0z9em","messageID":"msg_d7aa18fed001T0FSdcfzPD9VsD","sessionID":"ses_2855e993bffex8QV8kEBx24qSH","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-850498928d924f83ac506b3c2a2caca8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-026/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-026/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider |\n8: | Module | `cmd/cli` |\n9: | Language | Python |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 |\n12: \n13: This design defines the Kubernetes and AgentCube provider implementations for the AgentCube CLI toolkit. The providers enable deploying, managing, and invoking AI agents on Kubernetes through two deployment strategies:\n14: \n15: 1. **Standard Kubernetes** (`k8s`): Deployments + NodePort Services\n16: 2. **AgentCube Custom Resources** (`agentcube`): AgentRuntime CRs managed by Volcano AgentCube operators\n17: \n18: ---\n19: \n20: ## Architecture\n21: \n22: ### High-Level Flow\n23: \n24: ```\n25: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n26: │                         CLI Commands                                  │\n27: │  publish --provider=agentcube │ publish --provider=k8s               │\n28: │  invoke --provider=agentcube  │ invoke --provider=k8s                │\n29: │  status --provider=agentcube  │ status --provider=k8s                │\n30: └──────────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────────────┘\n31:                            │\n32:                            ▼\n33: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n34: │                       Runtime Layer                                   │\n35: │  PublishRuntime │ InvokeRuntime │ StatusRuntime                       │\n36: └──────────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────────────┘\n37:                            │\n38:            ┌───────────────┴───────────────┐\n39:            │                               │\n40:            ▼                               ▼\n41: ┌───────────────────────┐    ┌───────────────────────┐\n42: │   KubernetesProvider  │    │   AgentCubeProvider   │\n43: │   (Standard K8s)      │    │   (AgentRuntime CR)   │\n44: ├───────────────────────┤    ├───────────────────────┤\n45: │ - Deployment          │    │ - AgentRuntime CR     │\n46: │ - Service (NodePort)  │    │ - CustomObjectsApi    │\n47: │ - AppsV1Api           │    │ - CRD validation      │\n48: │ - CoreV1Api           │    │                       │\n49: └───────────────────────┘    └───────────────────────┘\n50:            │                               │\n51:            └───────────────┬───────────────┘\n52:                            │\n53:                            ▼\n54: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n55: │                    Kubernetes Cluster                                 │\n56: │  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────────────────┐     │\n57: │  │ Standard K8s     │  │ AgentCube CRD                        │     │\n58: │  │ - Deployment     │  │ - AgentRuntime CR                    │     │\n59: │  │ - NodePort SVC   │  │ - runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1a1  │     │\n60: │  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────────────────────────┘     │\n61: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n62: ```\n63: \n64: ### Package Layout\n65: \n66: | Path | Role |\n67: |------|------|\n68: | `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | `KubernetesProvider` - Standard K8s deployments |\n69: | `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | `AgentCubeProvider` - AgentRuntime CR management |\n70: | `agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | `PublishRuntime` - Orchestrates publish flow |\n71: | `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` | `InvokeRuntime` - Agent invocation logic |\n72: | `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` | `StatusRuntime` - Agent status retrieval |\n73: | `tests/test_k8s_provider.py` | Unit tests for KubernetesProvider |\n74: | `tests/test_agentcube_provider.py` | Unit tests for AgentCubeProvider |\n75: | `tests/test_publish_runtime.py` | Unit tests for PublishRuntime |\n76: | `tests/test_invoke_runtime.py` | Unit tests for InvokeRuntime |\n77: | `tests/test_status_runtime.py` | Unit tests for StatusRuntime |\n78: \n79: ---\n80: \n81: ## Data Structures\n82: \n83: ### KubernetesProvider Class\n84: \n85: ```python\n86: class KubernetesProvider:\n87:     NODE_PORT_MIN = 30000       # Kubernetes NodePort minimum\n88:     NODE_PORT_MAX = 32767       # Kubernetes NodePort maximum\n89:     DEFAULT_TIMEOUT = 120       # Deployment readiness timeout (seconds)\n90:     POLL_INTERVAL = 2           # Polling interval for readiness checks\n91: \n92:     namespace: str              # Target Kubernetes namespace\n93:     verbose: bool               # Enable verbose logging\n94:     _apps_api: AppsV1Api        # Kubernetes AppsV1Api client\n95:     _core_api: CoreV1Api        # Kubernetes CoreV1Api client\n96:     _logger: logging.Logger     # Module logger\n97: ```\n98: \n99: ### AgentCubeProvider Class\n100: \n101: ```python\n102: class AgentCubeProvider:\n103:     CR_GROUP = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"    # CustomResource group\n104:     CR_VERSION = \"v1alpha1\"                      # CustomResource version\n105:     CR_PLURAL = \"agentruntimes\"                  # CustomResource plural\n106:     SESSION_TIMEOUT = \"15m\"                      # Default session timeout\n107:     MAX_SESSION_DURATION = \"8h\"                  # Default max session duration\n108:     DEFAULT_SECRET = \"default-secret\"            # Default imagePullSecret name\n109: \n110:     namespace: str               # Target Kubernetes namespace\n111:     verbose: bool                # Enable verbose logging\n112:     _custom_api: CustomObjectsApi  # Kubernetes CustomObjectsApi client\n113:     _core_api: CoreV1Api         # Kubernetes CoreV1Api client\n114:     _logger: logging.Logger      # Module logger\n115: ```\n116: \n117: ### PublishRuntime Class\n118: \n119: ```python\n120: class PublishRuntime:\n121:     verbose: bool                           # Enable verbose logging\n122:     provider: str                            # Provider type (\"agentcube\" or \"k8s\")\n123:     _metadata_service: MetadataService      # Metadata management service\n124:     _docker_service: DockerService          # Docker operations service\n125:     _k8s_provider: KubernetesProvider       # Lazy-loaded for k8s provider\n126:     _agentcube_provider: AgentCubeProvider  # Lazy-loaded for agentcube provider\n127:     _logger: logging.Logger                 # Module logger\n128: ```\n129: \n130: ### InvokeRuntime Class\n131: \n132: ```python\n133: class InvokeRuntime:\n134:     verbose: bool                           # Enable verbose logging\n135:     provider: str                            # Provider type (\"agentcube\" or \"k8s\")\n136:     _metadata_service: MetadataService      # Metadata management service\n137:     _k8s_provider: KubernetesProvider       # Lazy-loaded for k8s provider\n138:     _agentcube_provider: AgentCubeProvider  # Lazy-loaded for agentcube provider\n139:     _logger: logging.Logger                 # Module logger\n140: ```\n141: \n142: ### StatusRuntime Class\n143: \n144: ```python\n145: class StatusRuntime:\n146:     verbose: bool                           # Enable verbose logging\n147:     provider: str                            # Provider type (\"agentcube\" or \"k8s\")\n148:     _metadata_service: MetadataService      # Metadata management service\n149:     _k8s_provider: KubernetesProvider       # Lazy-loaded for k8s provider\n150:     _agentcube_provider: AgentCubeProvider  # Lazy-loaded for agentcube provider\n151:     _logger: logging.Logger                 # Module logger\n152: ```\n153: \n154: ---\n155: \n156: ## API Contracts\n157: \n158: ### KubernetesProvider Interface\n159: \n160: #### `__init__`\n161: \n162: ```python\n163: def __init__(\n164:     self,\n165:     namespace: str = \"default\",\n166:     verbose: bool = False,\n167:     kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n168: ) -> None\n169: ```\n170: \n171: - **namespace**: Target namespace for deployments\n172: - **verbose**: Enable debug logging\n173: - **kubeconfig**: Custom kubeconfig path (falls back to incluster config)\n174: \n175: #### `deploy_agent`\n176: \n177: ```python\n178: def deploy_agent(\n179:     self,\n180:     agent_name: str,\n181:     image_url: str,\n182:     port: int,\n183:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n184:     replicas: int = 1,\n185:     node_port: Optional[int] = None,\n186:     env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n187: ) -> Dict[str, Any]\n188: ```\n189: \n190: - **Returns**: `{\"deployment_name\", \"service_name\", \"node_port\", \"service_url\", \"replicas\"}`\n191: - **Behavior**: Creates/patches Deployment and NodePort Service, waits for readiness\n192: \n193: #### `wait_for_deployment_ready`\n194: \n195: ```python\n196: def wait_for_deployment_ready(self, name: str, timeout: int = 120) -> None\n197: ```\n198: \n199: - **Raises**: `TimeoutError` if deployment not ready within timeout\n200: \n201: #### `get_agent_status`\n202: \n203: ```python\n204: def get_agent_status(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]\n205: ```\n206: \n207: - **Returns**: `{\"deployment\": {...}, \"service\": {...}}`\n208: \n209: #### `delete_agent`\n210: \n211: ```python\n212: def delete_agent(self, agent_name: str) -> Dict[str, Any]\n213: ```\n214: \n215: - **Returns**: `{\"deployment_deleted\": bool, \"service_deleted\": bool}`\n216: - **Behavior**: Ignores 404 errors (resource already deleted)\n217: \n218: #### `_sanitize_name`\n219: \n220: ```python\n221: def _sanitize_name(self, name: str) -> str\n222: ```\n223: \n224: - **Behavior**: Lowercase, replace non-alphanumeric with `-`, truncate to 63 chars, strip leading/trailing dashes\n225: - **Returns**: `\"default\"` if empty result\n226: \n227: ---\n228: \n229: ### AgentCubeProvider Interface\n230: \n231: #### `__init__`\n232: \n233: ```python\n234: def __init__(\n235:     self,\n236:     namespace: str = \"default\",\n237:     verbose: bool = False,\n238:     kubeconfig: Optional[str] = None,\n239: ) -> None\n240: ```\n241: \n242: #### `deploy_agent_runtime`\n243: \n244: ```python\n245: def deploy_agent_runtime(\n246:     self,\n247:     agent_name: str,\n248:     image_url: str,\n249:     port: int,\n250:     entrypoint: Optional[str] = None,\n251:     env_vars: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n252:     workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n253:     router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n254:     readiness_probe_path: Optional[str] = None,\n255:     readiness_probe_port: Optional[int] = None,\n256: ) -> Dict[str, Any]\n257: ```\n258: \n259: - **Returns**: `{\"deployment_name\", \"agent_id\", \"agent_endpoint\", \"status\"}`\n260: - **CR Spec**: Sets `sessionTimeout=\"15m\"`, `maxSessionDuration=\"8h\"`, `imagePullSecrets=[{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}]`\n261: - **Readiness Probe**: Default path `/health`, default port matches `port` argument\n262: \n263: #### `get_agent_runtime`\n264: \n265: ```python\n266: def get_agent_runtime(self, name: str, namespace: Optional[str] = None) -> Optional[Dict[str, Any]]\n267: ```\n268: \n269: - **Returns**: Full CR object or `None` if not found\n270: \n271: #### `delete_agent_runtime`\n272: \n273: ```python\n274: def delete_agent_runtime(self, name: str, namespace: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]\n275: ```\n276: \n277: - **Returns**: `{\"deleted\": bool, \"name\": str}` or `{\"deleted\": False, \"reason\": \"not_found\"}`\n278: \n279: ---\n280: \n281: ### PublishRuntime Interface\n282: \n283: #### `publish`\n284: \n285: ```python\n286: def publish(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]\n287: ```\n288: \n289: - **Options**: `version`, `image_url`, `image_username`, `image_password`, `description`, `region`, `namespace`, `node_port`, `replicas`\n290: - **Returns**: `{\"agent_name\", \"agent_id\", \"agent_endpoint\", \"deployment_type\", \"namespace\", \"k8s_deployment\", \"status\"}`\n291: - **Behavior**: Validates prerequisites, prepares image, deploys to K8s, updates metadata\n292: \n293: #### `_validate_publish_prerequisites`\n294: \n295: ```python\n296: def _validate_publish_prerequisites(\n297:     self, workspace_path: Path, metadata: AgentMetadata, options: Dict[str, Any]\n298: ) -> None\n299: ```\n300: \n301: - **Raises**: `ValueError` for missing required fields, `RuntimeError` for Docker unavailable\n302: \n303: ---\n304: \n305: ### InvokeRuntime Interface\n306: \n307: #### `invoke`\n308: \n309: ```python\n310: def invoke(\n311:     self,\n312:     workspace_path: Path,\n313:     payload: Dict[str, Any],\n314:     headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n315: ) -> Any\n316: ```\n317: \n318: - **Returns**: `{\"status_code\", \"response\", \"endpoint\", \"session_id\"}` (session_id if present in response headers)\n319: - **Behavior**: Rewrites endpoint for AgentRuntime CR to `/v1/namespaces/{ns}/agent-runtimes/{name}/invocations/`\n320: \n321: ---\n322: \n323: ### StatusRuntime Interface\n324: \n325: #### `get_status`\n326: \n327: ```python\n328: def get_status(self, workspace_path: Path, provider: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict[str, Any]\n329: ```\n330: \n331: - **Returns**: Status dict with keys depending on deployment type:\n332:   - `not_published`: `{\"status\", \"agent_name\", \"message\"}`\n333:   - `AgentRuntime`: `{\"status\", \"agent_name\", \"agent_id\", \"deployment_type\", \"namespace\", \"agent_endpoint\", \"cr_status\"}`\n334:   - `Deployment`: `{\"status\", \"agent_name\", \"deployment_type\", \"namespace\", \"deployment\", \"service\", \"agent_endpoint\", \"replicas\", \"available_replicas\"}`\n335: \n336: ---\n337: \n338: ## Error Handling\n339: \n340: ### Exception Types\n341: \n342: | Exception | Source | Scenario |\n343: |-----------|--------|----------|\n344: | `ValueError` | Providers/Runtime | Missing required configuration fields |\n345: | `RuntimeError` | Providers | Kubernetes API failures, deployment failures |\n346: | `TimeoutError` | KubernetesProvider | Deployment readiness timeout exceeded |\n347: | `kubernetes.client.exceptions.ApiException` | K8s SDK | API-level errors (404, 409, etc.) |\n348: \n349: ### Error Patterns\n350: \n351: #### Kubernetes API Errors\n352: \n353: ```python\n354: try:\n355:     result = api.create_namespaced_custom_object(...)\n356: except kubernetes.client.exceptions.ApiException as e:\n357:     if e.status == 409:\n358:         # Resource exists - patch instead\n359:         result = api.patch_namespaced_custom_object(...)\n360:     elif e.status == 404 and \"AgentRuntime\" in str(e):\n361:         raise ValueError(\"AgentRuntime CRD not installed. Install Volcano AgentCube CRDs\")\n362:     else:\n363:         raise RuntimeError(f\"Failed to deploy AgentRuntime CR: {e}\")\n364: ```\n365: \n366: #### Namespace Not Found\n367: \n368: ```python\n369: try:\n370:     core_api.read_namespace(name=namespace)\n371: except kubernetes.client.exceptions.ApiException as e:\n372:     if e.status == 404:\n373:         core_api.create_namespace(body=namespace_body)\n374:     else:\n375:         raise\n376: ```\n377: \n378: #### Delete Operations\n379: \n380: ```python\n381: try:\n382:     api.delete_namespaced_deployment(...)\n383:     deleted = True\n384: except kubernetes.client.exceptions.ApiException:\n385:     deleted = False  # Already deleted or not found - ignore\n386: ```\n387: \n388: ---\n389: \n390: ## Testing Strategy\n391: \n392: ### Unit Tests\n393: \n394: #### KubernetesProvider Tests\n395: \n396: | Test Class | Test Cases |\n397: |------------|------------|\n398: | `TestKubernetesProviderInit` | `test_init_default_namespace`, `test_init_custom_namespace`, `test_init_verbose` |\n399: | `TestSanitizeName` | `test_sanitize_name_lowercase`, `test_sanitize_name_replace_non_alphanumeric`, `test_sanitize_name_truncate_to_63_chars`, `test_sanitize_name_strip_dashes`, `test_sanitize_name_empty_string`, `test_sanitize_name_all_special_chars` |\n400: | `TestEnsureNamespace` | `test_ensure_namespace_exists`, `test_ensure_namespace_creates_if_not_exists` |\n401: | `TestCreateDeployment` | `test_create_deployment_basic`, `test_create_deployment_with_env_vars`, `test_create_deployment_with_entrypoint` |\n402: | `TestCreateService` | `test_create_service_basic`, `test_create_service_with_node_port`, `test_create_service_patch_if_exists` |\n403: | `TestWaitForDeploymentReady` | `test_wait_for_deployment_ready_success`, `test_wait_for_deployment_ready_timeout` |\n404: | `TestDeployAgent` | `test_deploy_agent_success` |\n405: | `TestGetAgentStatus` | `test_get_agent_status_success` |\n406: | `TestDeleteAgent` | `test_delete_agent_success` |\n407: | `TestNodePortValidation` | `test_node_port_min_boundary`, `test_node_port_max_boundary`, `test_default_timeout`, `test_poll_interval` |\n408: \n409: #### AgentCubeProvider Tests\n410: \n411: | Test Class | Test Cases |\n412: |------------|------------|\n413: | `TestAgentCubeProviderInit` | `test_init_default_namespace`, `test_init_custom_namespace`, `test_init_verbose`, `test_init_with_kubeconfig` |\n414: | `TestConstants` | `test_cr_group`, `test_cr_version`, `test_cr_plural`, `test_session_timeout`, `test_max_session_duration`, `test_default_secret` |\n415: | `TestSanitizeName` | Same pattern as KubernetesProvider |\n416: | `TestEnsureNamespace` | Same pattern as KubernetesProvider |\n417: | `TestDeployAgentRuntime` | `test_deploy_agent_runtime_success`, `test_deploy_agent_runtime_with_entrypoint`, `test_deploy_agent_runtime_patch_existing`, `test_deploy_agent_runtime_crd_not_found`, `test_deploy_agent_runtime_with_env_vars` |\n418: | `TestGetAgentRuntime` | `test_get_agent_runtime_success`, `test_get_agent_runtime_not_found`, `test_get_agent_runtime_custom_namespace` |\n419: | `TestDeleteAgentRuntime` | `test_delete_agent_runtime_success`, `test_delete_agent_runtime_not_found` |\n420: | `TestReadinessProbe` | `test_readiness_probe_default_values`, `test_readiness_probe_custom_values` |\n421: | `TestImagePullSecrets` | `test_image_pull_secrets_default` |\n422: \n423: ### Test Patterns\n424: \n425: All tests use `unittest.mock` to mock Kubernetes API calls:\n426: \n427: ```python\n428: def test_example(self) -> None:\n429:     with patch(\"kubernetes.config.load_kube_config\"):\n430:         mock_custom_api = MagicMock()\n431:         mock_custom_api.create_namespaced_custom_object.return_value = {\"metadata\": {\"name\": \"test\"}}\n432:         \n433:         with patch(\"kubernetes.client.CustomObjectsApi\", return_value=mock_custom_api):\n434:             with patch(\"kubernetes.client.CoreV1Api\"):\n435:                 provider = AgentCubeProvider()\n436:                 provider._custom_api = mock_custom_api\n437:                 # Test logic here\n438: ```\n439: \n440: ### Integration Tests\n441: \n442: Integration tests require:\n443: - Running Kubernetes cluster (or kind/minikube)\n444: - Volcano AgentCube CRDs installed for AgentCubeProvider tests\n445: - Valid kubeconfig or incluster config\n446: \n447: ---\n448: \n449: ## File Structure\n450: \n451: ```\n452: cmd/cli/\n453: ├── agentcube/\n454: │   ├── services/\n455: │   │   ├── __init__.py\n456: │   │   ├── k8s_provider.py          # KubernetesProvider (342 lines)\n457: │   │   ├── agentcube_provider.py    # AgentCubeProvider (190 lines)\n458: │   │   ├── metadata_service.py      # Metadata management\n459: │   │   └── docker_service.py        # Docker operations\n460: │   ├── runtime/\n461: │   │   ├── __init__.py\n462: │   │   ├── publish_runtime.py       # PublishRuntime (271 lines)\n463: │   │   ├── invoke_runtime.py        # InvokeRuntime (117 lines)\n464: │   │   └── status_runtime.py        # StatusRuntime (157 lines)\n465: │   │   ├── pack_runtime.py          # PackRuntime\n466: │   │   └── build_runtime.py         # BuildRuntime\n467: │   ├── models/\n468: │   │   ├── __init__.py\n469: │   │   └── pack_models.py           # MetadataOptions\n470: │   └── cli/\n471: │       ├── __init__.py\n472: │       └── main.py                   # Typer CLI commands\n473: ├── tests/\n474: │   ├── __init__.py\n475: │   ├── test_k8s_provider.py         # KubernetesProvider unit tests (373 lines)\n476: │   ├── test_agentcube_provider.py   # AgentCubeProvider unit tests (446 lines)\n477: │   ├── test_publish_runtime.py\n478: │   ├── test_invoke_runtime.py\n479: │   ├── test_status_runtime.py\n480: │   └── ...\n481: ├── examples/\n482: │   ├── hello-agent/\n483: │   │   └── main.py\n484: │   └── math-agent/\n485: │   │   └── main.py\n486: └── pyproject.toml\n487: ```\n488: \n489: ---\n490: \n491: ## Dependencies\n492: \n493: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n494: |---------|---------|---------|\n495: | `kubernetes` | >=28.0.0 | Kubernetes Python SDK (AppsV1Api, CoreV1Api, CustomObjectsApi) |\n496: | `httpx` | >=0.24.0 | Async HTTP client for invoke operations |\n497: | `pydantic` | >=2.0.0 | Metadata validation (AgentMetadata) |\n498: | `typer[all]` | >=0.9.0 | CLI framework |\n499: | `rich` | >=13.0.0 | Rich console output |\n500: \n501: ### Optional Dependencies\n502: \n503: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n504: |---------|---------|---------|\n505: | `pytest` | >=7.4.0 | Testing framework |\n506: | `pytest-asyncio` | >=0.21.0 | Async test support |\n507: | `pytest-mock` | >=3.11.0 | Mock fixtures |\n508: \n509: ---\n510: \n511: ## Implementation Notes\n512: \n513: ### Constants\n514: \n515: #### KubernetesProvider\n516: ```python\n517: NODE_PORT_MIN = 30000     # Per Kubernetes spec\n518: NODE_PORT_MAX = 32767     # Per Kubernetes spec\n519: DEFAULT_TIMEOUT = 120     # Seconds to wait for deployment readiness\n520: POLL_INTERVAL = 2         # Seconds between readiness checks\n521: ```\n522: \n523: #### AgentCubeProvider\n524: ```python\n525: CR_GROUP = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"\n526: CR_VERSION = \"v1alpha1\"\n527: CR_PLURAL = \"agentruntimes\"\n528: SESSION_TIMEOUT = \"15m\"           # Default session timeout\n529: MAX_SESSION_DURATION = \"8h\"       # Maximum session duration\n530: DEFAULT_SECRET = \"default-secret\" # Default imagePullSecret\n531: ```\n532: \n533: ### Name Sanitization\n534: \n535: Both providers use identical sanitization logic:\n536: 1. Convert to lowercase\n537: 2. Replace non-alphanumeric characters with `-`\n538: 3. Collapse multiple dashes to single dash\n539: 4. Strip leading/trailing dashes\n540: 5. Truncate to 63 characters (Kubernetes name limit)\n541: 6. Return `\"default\"` if result is empty\n542: \n543: ### Lazy Provider Loading\n544: \n545: Runtime classes lazily import providers to avoid import errors when kubernetes package is not installed:\n546: \n547: ```python\n548: if provider == \"k8s\":\n549:     from agentcube.services.k8s_provider import KubernetesProvider\n550:     self._k8s_provider = KubernetesProvider(verbose=verbose)\n551: elif provider == \"agentcube\":\n552:     from agentcube.services.agentcube_provider import AgentCubeProvider\n553:     self._agentcube_provider = AgentCubeProvider(verbose=verbose)\n554: else:\n555:     raise ValueError(f\"Invalid provider: {provider}. Must be 'agentcube' or 'k8s'\")\n556: ```\n557: \n558: ### Endpoint Rewriting for AgentRuntime\n559: \n560: When invoking an AgentRuntime CR, the endpoint URL is rewritten:\n561: \n562: ```python\n563: # Original endpoint from metadata\n564: endpoint = metadata.agent_endpoint\n565: \n566: # Rewritten for AgentRuntime CR\n567: sanitized_name = self._agentcube_provider._sanitize_name(metadata.agent_name)\n568: namespace = k8s_deployment.get(\"namespace\", \"default\")\n569: base_endpoint = endpoint.rstrip(\"/\")\n570: endpoint = f\"{base_endpoint}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{sanitized_name}/invocations/\"\n571: ```\n572: \n573: ### Session ID Management\n574: \n575: The invoke flow manages session IDs bidirectionally:\n576: 1. **Request**: Adds `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` header if metadata contains `session_id`\n577: 2. **Response**: Extracts `x-agentcube-session-id` from response headers and persists to metadata\n578: \n579: ---\n580: \n581: ## References\n582: \n583: - cli-toolkit/design.md — CLI toolkit architecture\n584: - cli-toolkit/spec.md — CLI specification\n585: - deployment/client-go.md — Kubernetes client-go library reference\n586: - python-sdk/spec.md — AgentCube Python SDK specification\n\n(End of file - total 586 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-026 — K8s/AgentCube Provider |\n| Module | `cmd/cli` |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\nThis design defines the Kubernetes and AgentCube provider implementations for the AgentCube CLI toolkit. The providers enable deploying, managing, and invoking AI agents on Kubernetes through two deployment strategies:\n\n1. **Standard Kubernetes** (`k8s`): Deployments + NodePort Services\n2. **AgentCube Custom Resources** (`agentcube`): AgentRuntime CRs managed by Volcano AgentCube operators\n\n---\n\n## Architecture","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-026/design.md","time":{"start":1775878917504,"end":1775878917525}}}}
